name: Let's Skank
description:
This is the "Yellow Swirl" version. The original painting was mixed media on wood. This guy unintentionally ended up looking like Tim Armstrong to me, from Operation Ivy and Rancid fame, which should explain the title, “Let’s Skank”. According to Urban Dicitonary:
“Skanking” – The bizarre, wild dance done to the music known as Ska. Not to be confused with a, “skank” skanking resembles running in place while flailing your arms. While popular at Ska shows, it is more acceptable at other mixed venues to simply join the mosh. Unskilled skankers are sometimes mistaken for seizure victims. This NFT is a 1/1, which means only one of these will be minted to the blockchain. There are 2 different color versions available, but only 1 of each, so they are totally unique originals. I hope you enjoy it! Twitter: @jeffclaassen - Instagram: @jeffclaassen
